.SH "NAME"
g\-var \- Produce (OpenGL) Vertex Arrays from BOT BRL\-CAD geometry
.SH "SYNOPSIS"
.sp
\fBg\-var\fP [\-v] [\-y] [\-s \fIscale\fP] [\-f] [\-o \fIoutfile\fP] \fIinfile.g\fP \fIobject\fP
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
.sp
\fBg\-var\fP writes the bag of triangle (BOT) primitives of the
specified \fIobject\fP in a binary array format to \fIoutfile\fP or to
\fIstdout\fP.
.SH "OPTIONS"
.sp
\fB\-v\fP
.RS 4
Request verbose output.
.RE
.sp
\fB\-y\fP
.RS 4
Transform the coordinate system from xyz to xzy.
.RE
.sp
\fB\-s\fP \f(CRscale\fP
.RS 4
Scale the output geometry by factor \fIscale\fP. By
default the scale factor is 0.001 (standard transformation from meters
to millimeters).
.RE
.sp
\fB\-f\fP
.RS 4
Flip face normals. This changes both the vertex order and the
output normals.
.RE
.sp
\fB\-o\fP \fIoutfile\fP
.RS 4
The output will be written to \fIoutfile\fP. By default
the output is written to stdout.
.RE
.SH "FILE FORMAT"
.sp
\fITODO\fP
.SH "EXAMPLE"
.sp
.if n .RS 4
.nf
$ g\-var \-o sample.mesh sample.g sample_object
.fi
